comment.body:
In theory building on the host then copying it over to the image would be fine in most cases. The case that I think this could be an issue is if you build profiling on macOS. You would get a Mach-O binary rather than an ELF binary, and it would cause other issues.

I might be able to get away with using a relative path. I did an absolute path as part of debugging an issue. I'll do a quick test and I'll let you know.
